# Styling Lists ğŸ’…

You can use CSS to make lists look like menus or navigation bars.

- `list-style-type: none;`: Removes bullets/numbers.
- `display: inline;`: Makes items horizontal.
- `padding` and `margin`: Adjust spacing.

```css
ul {
  list-style-type: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin: 0;
}
li {
  display: inline;
  margin-right: 20px;
}
```

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<style>
ul {
  list-style-type: none;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: #333333;
}

li {
  float: left;
}

li a {
  display: block;
  color: white;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 16px;
  text-decoration: none;
}

li a:hover {
  background-color: #111111;
}
</style>
<body>

<ul>
  <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
  <li><a href="#news">News</a></li>
  <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
  <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
</ul>

</body>
</html>
